<table name="125" class="ControlTable" cellSpacing="0" cellPadding="0" width="100%" align="center">
	<tr bgColor="#666666">
		<td align="left" width="20"><IMG src="images/mini_t.gif">
		</td>
		<td class="TextBanner" style="FONT-SIZE: 18pt" align="left" width="600">
			Rallos Zek DEAD!
		</td>
		<TD style="FONT-SIZE: 7pt" align="right">
			1/18/2003
			<br>
			Kaitlynn
		</TD>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="TextNormal" colspan="3" width="100%">
			<p align="center"><img src="images/011803/RallosHead.jpg" width="550" height="347" border="0"></p>
            <p>Talisman really stepped it up these last two weeks. We decided 
              it was time for a challenge, instead of the endless flagging and 
              easy loot, so we set our sights on Rallos Zek.</p>
            <p>At first it seemed like nothing had changed. The first night we 
              attempted the Rallos ring, we got the doors opened and received 
              our &quot;surprises.&quot; We all laughed hysterically while staring 
              at the &quot;Loading, please wait&quot; message that appeared simultaneously 
              on all our screens. For those 5 of you who have not scoured the 
              boards for walkthroughs, don't. Really. Some of this stuff is so 
              fun, you're doing yourselves a real disservice by spoiling it. The 
              suprise factor of what happened after we opened those doors was 
              well worth it.</p>
            <table class="TextNormal" width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4">
              <tr>
                <td><img src="images/011803/MiniRallos.jpg" width="250" height="458"></td>
                <td><p><b>The next night, we began work on the &quot;suprises.&quot; 
                    Two attempts, and got one done. Feeling pretty good! Night 
                    three, and we are able to take care of both surprises and 
                    move into Rallos Zek's Secret Tactical Lair!</b></p>
                  <p><b>Not only did we make it into his lair - we killed him! Wow, 
                    only our third night of trying and its onward to face Rallos 
                    Zek the Warlord!</b></p>
                  <p><b>Not having any idea whatsoever about what we were about to face, we 
                    engaged the mighty Rallos Zek ... and got our asses handed 
                    to us in about 1 minute. Didn't even dent him heh.</b></p></td>
              </tr>
            </table>
            <p>Night four, and we head back in to finish the job. And that's when 
              we discover the &quot;nuances&quot; of this fabulously programmed 
              event. For about the next week, we discovered every possible way 
              to screw it up. We also discovered every possible way that Verant's 
              stellar coding team allowed unsuspecting visitors in an xp zone 
              to add to the excitement. The ring was never the same twice.</p>
            <p align="center"><img src="images/011803/PitMobsInc.gif" width="307" height="127"></p>
            <p align="center"><img src="images/011803/PitTrain.jpg" width="450" height="241"></p>
            <p>Days went by with attempt after attempt being made to get back 
              to where we had been only a few days earlier. Finally on Thursday, 
              we once again got through the intermediate stages of the ring to 
              again face Rallos Zek himself.</p>
            <p>Once the raid was officially dead we all awaited the news - how 
              close did we get him!?!?! 86%. Well, not exactly thrilling - but 
              it was progress. So Friday we trudged back in again. First attempt 
              got us to an incredible 18% health! We can do this! Second attempt 
              ...</p>
            <p align="center"><img src="images/011803/RallosZek025.jpg" width="154" height="30"><img src="images/011803/RallosZek012.jpg" width="153" height="28"><img src="images/011803/RallosZek004.jpg" width="155" height="27"> 
              <img src="images/011803/RallosDeathEmote.jpg" width="388" height="47"></p>
            <p align="center"><img src="images/011803/RallosLootGrimfacedVisor.jpg" width="400" height="162"></p>
            <p>Loot was two of these masks. Our first Rallos Zek loot went to 
              Malloci and Marron. Congrats!</p>
            <p>And a big congrats to the entire guild for pulling together and 
              hitting this event every day for almost two weeks (save a patch 
              day and zone-crash). It was amazing to be part of a group who set 
              their minds to working out a solution and learning an event through 
              sheer determination. Well done all!</p>

<p></p>
      <p><b><h4>What would an update be without embarassing quotes</h4></b></p>
      <p align="center">Beldon learns the dangers of speaking near npcs<br>
        <img src="images/011803/BeldonQuote1.gif" width="394" height="121"> </p>
      <p align="center">Raid orders are always very specific<br>
        <img src="images/011803/IhsanRaidQuote.gif" width="405" height="34"> </p>
      <p align="center">With Martha Stewart in trouble, Qhue steps up to teach 
        us crafts<br>
        <img src="images/011803/QhueCandy.gif" width="401" height="72"> </p>
      <p align="center">Proof that TV will rot your brain<br>
        <img src="images/011803/TarmQuote1.gif" width="391" height="36"> </p>
      <p align="center">And finally<br>
        <img src="images/011803/Cynosure.gif" width="403" height="34"></p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>

