<table name="124" class="ControlTable" cellSpacing="0" cellPadding="0" width="100%" align="center">
	<tr bgColor="#666666">
		<td align="left" width="20"><IMG src="images/mini_t.gif">
		</td>
		<td class="TextBanner" style="FONT-SIZE: 18pt" align="left" width="600">
			You're in MY World Now!
		</td>
		<TD style="FONT-SIZE: 7pt" align="right">
			1/2/2003
			<br>
			Kaitlynn
		</TD>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="TextNormal" colspan="3" width="100%">
			<table width="100%" border="0"><tr><td class="TextNormal">
            <p><img src="images/010203/SolRoHeader.jpg" width="550" height="275" border="0"></p>
            <p>After an eternity it seemed of running from one encounter to the 
              next and listening to our resident QuestGnome Qhue tell us &quot;Ok, 
              after this one we'll be able to advance.&quot; [Bzzzzt] &quot;Well, 
              ok, after the <strong>next</strong> flag I swear we can advance,&quot; 
              we finally made it into Sol Ro's Tower! </p>
            <p>After some initial pokes and forays into the zone, we set up a 
              full-fledged exploratory &quot;How far can we get&quot; raid last 
              night. The results? Several bosses / mini-bosses down! Only problem 
              we ran into was people needing sleep, so we had to call it a night. 
              Hell even with boss encounters I don't think we had more than a 
              handfull of deaths all night, and those were usually from the pull 
              team. Soon I suspect, we'll set up another raid and advance all 
              the way! (Don't quote me on what constitutes a boss or mini-boss. 
              I see something &quot;named,&quot; then it's important in my book!) 
              :) </p>
            <p>And what about these boss/mini-boss encounters? In a word - lame. 
              A couple of the most beautiful mobs I have ever seen, and yet the 
              encounters were dull and boring. No imagination put into them whatsoever. 
              And no deaths. We're uber, but come on, it's got to be a dull encounter 
              when it can't even kill a hobbit.</p>
            <p><img src="images/010203/Xuzl.jpg" width="500" height="437"></p>
            <p><a href="images/010203/ArlyxirSide.jpg"><img src="images/010203/Arlyxir.jpg" width="500" height="270" border="0"></a><br>
              <font size="-1">Click for a nice side shot!</font></p>
            <p>Any loot you ask? Hehehe yeah. For the most part, the loot was 
              pretty craptastic. I guess it goes along with the nature of the 
              encounters. Mr. Diablo Reject dropped some uber Paly loot. And not 
              just one but TWO! The guild was ecstatic let me tell you. I wasn't 
              paying a lot of attention to the loot so didn't get many pictures. 
              Mostly it was &quot;click the link [crap] move on.&quot; or click 
              it and find out it's the wrong class for me. Elis did pick up a 
              nice <a href="images/010203/HoodedSanguineMantle.jpg">Hooded Sanguine 
              Mantle</a> though, and Yikten got a <a href="images/010203/SphereOfEncasedFlame.jpg">Sphere 
              of Encased Flame</a>. I know an Ornate BP pattern dropped and I 
              think I recall something dropping an <strong>Etheral</strong> parchment 
              too. WooHoo!</p>
            <p><img src="images/010203/LanceOfTheFlameKnight.jpg" width="550" height="369"><br>
              Kable says "Hammie, I have something neeewwwww!"</p>

	  <p></p>
            <p><b>Candid Saryrn</b></p>
            <p><a href="images/010203/SaryrnBefore.jpg"><img src="images/010203/SaryrnAfter.jpg" width="200" height="404" border="0" align="left"></a></p>
            <p>You guys are all drooling over Saryrn. I know it, I've seen you 
              doing it! Pretty sad when we go to get a flag from her and even 
              the wizards all run up to her &quot;just to make sure they're in 
              range.&quot; Uh-huh.</p>
            <p>Let me let you in on a little secret. You have no idea how hard 
              it is for her to look so good at being so bad. As a reality check, 
              just click to see an undoctored hidden camera shot of her after 
              she wakes up in the morning.</p>
            <p>(Donations to the recovery fund for our intrepid Talisman photographer 
              can be made through the guild officers.)</p>

</td></tr></table> 
